  <description type="morphology">Herbs, perennial. Stems: basal not produced; flowering erect, 25–60 cm, spreading-villous. Leaves of flowering stems alternate; blade lanceolate to elliptic-lanceolate, 5–8 × 1–3 mm, apex acute, abaxial surface villous on midvein and margins, adaxial glabrous. Pedicels 1 per axil, 1–1.5 mm. Flowers: calyx 1.3–1.5 mm, &lt;usually lightly colored basally&gt;, outer sepals shorter than inner. Capsules ellipsoid, 1.8–2 × 1.6–1.7 mm, longer than calyx. Seeds 1(–3), &lt;membranous coat white&gt;.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering spring; fruiting summer–fall.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Dry, open sand-scrub and flatwoods;</description>
