  <discussion type="conservation">of conservation concern;</discussion>
  <discussion>Lechea divaricata is endemic to peninsular Florida but apparently absent from the Florida Keys. A report of L. divaricata from Alabama was based on a misidentified specimen of L. mucronata (D. D. Spaulding 2013).</discussion>
